The paper proposes a new graph convolution method that improves performance on a wide range of supervised and unsupervised tasks. This work is closely related to graph neural networks and combines the strengths of both spatial and spectral methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of graph-based models and algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with graph structures and their properties, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper includes experiments on image datasets, which could suggest a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
